title: Single-cell RNA sequecing of E13.5 mouse cerebella
abstract: In this study we performed single-cell sequencing of E13.5 mouse cerebella, revealing different newly generated neurons and their associated molecular features.
overall_design: Design: Single-cell suspensions were prepared using Accumax digestion followed by manual trituration using a Pasteur pipette. Cells were processed with the 10X Genomics Chromium Single Cell Kit Version 1
summary: In this study we performed single-cell sequencing of E13.5 mouse cerebella, revealing different newly generated neurons and their associated molecular features.
